# PulangAman API deploy procedure

## Local dev

```bash
cd services/api
npm install
npm run migrate   # needs DATABASE_URL in .env
npm run dev
```

Health: `curl http://127.0.0.1:3000/health`

## Production (Render)

- Service: `pulangaman-api` — root `services/api`, auto-deploy on push to `main`
- Build: `npm ci --include=dev && npm run build`
- Start: `npm run migrate && node dist/index.js`
- Health: `https://pulangaman-api.onrender.com/health`

After pushing API changes:

1. `git push origin main`
2. Poll `/health` until `ok: true` (cold start can take ~30–50s)
3. Tell the user to rebuild the Flutter app if endpoints or response shapes changed

## Auth mode

Mobile currently uses **dev-auth** (`Bearer dev:<uid>`). `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` on Render should stay empty until Firebase login ships in the app.

## Do not

- Skip migrations on production (handled by `startCommand`)
- Commit `.env` or credentials
- Assume mobile picks up API changes without a new APK when response contracts change
